        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(codesandbox): add CodeSandbox provider",
        "body": "Closes #334\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds a built-in `codesandbox` delegated-run provider backed by the CodeSandbox SDK. The provider can create and reuse Crabbox-owned SDK VM Sandboxes, sync the local checkout through the SDK file bridge, run commands, list/status/stop sandboxes, hibernate/resume, and expose provider-owned preview URLs through the ports/hosts SDK surfaces.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Adds `internal/providers/codesandbox` with env-only auth, local claim ownership checks, SDK bridge/client code, archive sync, lifecycle commands, pause/resume, ports, and cleanup.\n- Registers the provider and updates config/flags, command docs, provider metadata, and the generated provider matrix.\n- Runs the local Node SDK bridge from a trusted Crabbox cache directory with a minimal environment and prepares `@codesandbox/sdk` there with npm.\n- Keeps the CodeSandbox API token out of persistent config and argv.\n- Keeps forwarded command env values out of local argv and remote command text by staging them through a temporary remote env file before exec.\n\n## Review Fixes\n\n- Hardened trusted-only bridge config so repo config cannot replace the token-bearing bridge executable or SDK package.\n- Made missing remote ownership tags fail closed before mutating or deleting remote sandboxes.\n- Preserved empty command args and string command output from the SDK.\n- Increased bridge timeout/capture limits for long or noisy delegated runs.\n- Corrected SDK command/create option shapes and sync archive paths.\n- Removed the misleading URL bridge capability while keeping ports URL output.\n- Ensured read-only status/get paths do not resume hibernated sandboxes.\n- Made live-smoke diagnostic failures exit nonzero except for explicit environment blockers.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/providers/codesandbox`\n- `go test ./internal/providers/codesandbox ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `go test -race ./internal/providers/codesandbox ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `node scripts/check-docs-links.mjs`\n- `node scripts/check-command-docs.mjs`\n- `node scripts/generate-provider-matrix.mjs --check`\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `./bin/crabbox providers --json`\n- no-auth negative check for `crabbox doctor --provider codesandbox --json`\n- `node scripts/live-codesandbox-smoke.test.js`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `~/.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\nLive CodeSandbox smoke is credential-gated and currently classifies cleanly as `environment_blocked reason=missing_CRABBOX_CODESANDBOX_API_KEY_or_CSB_API_KEY` when no CodeSandbox API key is present.\n",
